TOPIC: PURPOSE AND PRE-LAID PATHS

The Question About Purpose

• Question: "Regarding purpose... your purpose"

Bashar's Answer on Purpose

• Same as everyone's purpose: TO BE YOURSELF AS FULLY AS YOU CAN
• The idea of acting on your highest excitement is an indication of the expression of your purpose
• But your purpose is to be you as fully as you can
• "Is that too simple?" "Yes." "Then you may complicate it however you wish."

The Question About Pre-Laid Paths

• "Do we, as human beings, before we come to this life and experience what we're experiencing, do we come with a pre-laid out path?"

Bashar's Answer on Themes and Free Will

**In Some Senses, Many of You Do:**
• Although it's not necessarily as rigid as you may think
• There are certain THEMES that you decide to explore
• You could consider those themes a type of destiny if you wish

**But Your Free Will Determines How:**
• Your free will determines HOW you will explore that theme
• You can explore it:
  - Happy
  - Sad
  - Upside down
  - Backwards
  - Forwards
  - Fast or slow
  - Whatever you wish according to your free will

**You Will Explore the Theme:**
• But you WILL explore the theme that you set out for yourselves
• Because that's the definition of the life
• The process you go through in discovering yourself from that particular angle, that particular path
• Is the very essence of why you are you as this particular persona in this life

Working Both Ends

• So you work both ends of it in a sense:
  - By making a choice from a higher level
  - Then making choices with your free will once you are in the physical experience
  - Exploring the theme that was chosen from the other level

The Linear Perspective vs. Reality

• From a linear point of view, it seems as if:
  - You are a spirit before the life
  - Then you choose to have a life
  - Then you die and leave the life
• But that's just your perspective from a physical point of view
• All these stages of your existence actually all exist simultaneously
• But you don't have to worry about that right now

