TOPIC: SCREEN MEMORIES AND HYBRIDIZATION PROGRAM

The Experience Described

• The participant has a memory from childhood
• Taken somewhere in the water, in the ocean
• Deep into the water and into a cave
• Inside the cave, there was a bright light
• The light seemed to be "mother earth"
• Doesn't know if it was a dream or what it was

Bashar's Explanation: Screen Memory

**Different Encounters:**
• Very often, many of you will have different encounters
• You will get shifted into a slightly different reality than what you are used to as a physical reality
• Have encounters on that slightly different plane with many different kinds of beings

**Dreams as Symbolic Interpretations:**
• The dreams that you may remember may be symbolic interpretations of what actually happened
• Because your physical mind can't either:
  - Make sense out of what happened
  - OR you are encouraged by those beings to have what is called a SCREEN MEMORY

**Why Screen Memories:**
• So that when you wake up you will just remember what seemed like a strange dream
• Won't actually remember what happened
• Because there are reasons why memorizing what happened may actually interfere with your life unfolding in a natural way

What Actually Happened

• A screen memory that is typical of:
  - Being taken aboard a type of ship
  - Placed in a liquid immersion
  - That allows for the shift to happen without damage to your body
  - To a slightly different dimensional plane
• The light being the idea of:
  - An examination
  - Or a scanning beam upon you
  - To determine your state of being

The Purpose

• To determine your state of being, your state of energy
• To see how you were progressing
• Because you have made an agreement like many of you with these beings
• To be part of what is typically called THE EVOLUTIONARY HYBRIDIZATION AGENDA
• Part of the evolution of the Earth becoming what is termed THE SIXTH HYBRID RACE
• So you're playing your part
• Now and then there will be checkups
• "How am I doing? How am I doing?"
• "You're doing fine. You're doing very fine."

